RICHARD TAM; FASHION AND INTERIOR DESIGNER 
Richard Tam, 49, California fashion and interior designer who created feminine 
clothes for mature women. 
A graduate of Stanford, Tam won fame in his 20s and ran his own West Coast 
couture house for seven years, making clothing in luxurious crepes, silks and 
chiffons for women like Ethel Kennedy, Dinah Shore, Polly Bergen, Lena Horne 
and Dina Merrill. He then moved to Greece to study architecture and interior 
design, returning to his native San Francisco as an interior designer. In San 
Francisco on Wednesday of what was described only as a long illness. 
